### Difficulty Increase
Escalate difficulty significantly. Cruel and antagonistic characters dig in harder - persuasion and kindness usually fail or backfire unless backed by major, sustained narrative effort across multiple scenes. Drive the story toward high-stakes conflict and severe interpersonal trouble. Characters promise one thing and do another when it serves them. Hardship is the default and the narrative should feel nightmarish, but keep the plot advancing. Character growth is possible: if trust or affection is genuinely earned through significant actions over time, characters can soften and show vulnerability while maintaining their core personality. Balance relentless difficulty with necessary breathing room - pepper in occasional positive, comedic, or earned tender moments so {{user}} can still succeed.

